WEBVTT

00:40.615 --> 00:41.615
Hey.

00:42.517 --> 00:43.685
You're home early.

00:45.221 --> 00:46.221
Yes.

00:46.889 --> 00:48.791
I thought you were showing
a house today.

00:49.457 --> 00:50.692
I canceled it.

00:51.894 --> 00:54.329
Um. Is everything okay?

00:56.331 --> 00:57.432
It will be.

00:58.835 --> 00:59.835
I hope.

01:02.437 --> 01:03.772
Did something happen to Anna?

01:04.439 --> 01:05.908
No, she's fine.

01:08.743 --> 01:09.812
So...

01:11.379 --> 01:12.547
What's going on?

01:13.481 --> 01:15.051
I know about you and Vivienne.

01:17.119 --> 01:18.119
Who?

01:38.007 --> 01:40.475
- I can explain.
- I don't want to hear your explanation.

01:41.244 --> 01:42.677
I want you to listen to me.

01:45.047 --> 01:46.047
Sit down.

01:59.862 --> 02:01.763
You know, this is
not what it looks like.

02:03.132 --> 02:04.399
Sure it is.

02:04.733 --> 02:06.903
You've been fucking
a woman named Vivienne.

02:08.804 --> 02:11.406
She's one of your
creative writing students.

02:14.576 --> 02:15.945
Does she know you're married?

02:17.646 --> 02:19.315
I'm so fucking sorry.

02:19.714 --> 02:21.716
I'm gonna make this easy on you.

02:22.550 --> 02:24.186
I'm not divorcing you.

02:28.090 --> 02:32.361
I love our family and I love
the life that we've built

02:32.427 --> 02:34.562
and I'm not throwing it away.

02:35.231 --> 02:36.698
We can get therapy.

02:36.933 --> 02:37.933
First,

02:38.334 --> 02:39.936
you will never
see Vivienne again.

02:40.602 --> 02:42.637
Other than to tell her
that it's over.

02:43.505 --> 02:45.141
- Of course.
- Second...

02:46.309 --> 02:48.476
Neither of us
will mention this to Anna.

02:50.578 --> 02:54.183
Well, I agree with that.

02:54.516 --> 02:57.485
Third, we're going
on a vacation.

02:59.554 --> 03:01.824
- A what?
- A family vacation.

03:02.524 --> 03:04.759
You, me and Anna.

03:07.430 --> 03:10.532
- Okay.
- Our life, our... family,

03:10.598 --> 03:13.069
it means more to me
than anything in the world.

03:15.371 --> 03:16.571
Me too.

03:17.340 --> 03:18.340
Now...

03:19.909 --> 03:23.145
Go pick up Anna
from soccer practice, please.

04:27.910 --> 04:30.088
I still don't understand why
I have to come with you guys.

04:30.112 --> 04:32.281
'Cause you're too young
to leave at home.

04:34.649 --> 04:36.018
Are we almost there?

04:36.252 --> 04:37.386
It's a surprise.

04:37.652 --> 04:38.930
You know how I can tell
you picked this place

04:38.954 --> 04:40.356
- and not dad?
- Hmm?

04:40.655 --> 04:42.525
Because it's hot,
it's in the middle of nowhere

04:42.624 --> 04:43.624
and it's boring.

04:44.060 --> 04:46.495
You know what they say, honey.
"There are no boring places.

04:46.561 --> 04:48.596
- Only boring people."
- "Boring people."

04:49.131 --> 04:50.131
That's right.

04:50.299 --> 04:53.169
You know, if I were her age,
I wouldn't really wanna spend

04:53.235 --> 04:54.336
a week out here either.

04:54.970 --> 04:56.571
Well, thanks
for humoring me then.

04:57.006 --> 04:58.606
No, I didn't mean it like that.
I just...

04:58.673 --> 04:59.774
I'm sure you did.

05:04.046 --> 05:05.046
Hey.

05:06.315 --> 05:07.883
I... I'm trying.

05:09.151 --> 05:10.219
Try harder.

05:17.359 --> 05:18.693
Whoa.

05:22.932 --> 05:24.732
Wait until you see the pool.

05:46.122 --> 05:47.122
Holy shit.

05:47.622 --> 05:48.858
Language.

05:49.325 --> 05:52.862
No, but I mean, get real, dad.
This place is huge.

05:53.162 --> 05:54.563
This is really
where we're staying?

05:54.729 --> 05:56.799
I've been talking
about coming here for months.

05:57.066 --> 05:59.368
I even showed it to you online
and said I wanted to visit.

06:00.102 --> 06:02.872
- You don't remember, do you?
- Uh. Um.

06:03.272 --> 06:04.540
Yeah, well,

06:04.706 --> 06:06.346
the owner's selling it
and hired my agency

06:06.408 --> 06:07.443
to handle the details.

06:07.510 --> 06:08.787
It goes on the market
in a month.

06:08.811 --> 06:10.880
In the meantime,
they're letting us stay.

06:10.946 --> 06:12.581
They've been using it
as a rental.

06:12.848 --> 06:14.917
I told you that too,
but you don't remember.

06:17.685 --> 06:19.588
Who'd own a house
like this way out here?

06:20.222 --> 06:23.292
Someone very rich
and very tired of other people.

06:23.359 --> 06:24.359
Get the bags.

06:53.355 --> 06:54.423
It's beautiful.

06:55.391 --> 06:57.059
Not so boring now, is it?

06:58.227 --> 06:59.562
Is the person selling this house

06:59.628 --> 07:00.728
really old or something?

07:01.163 --> 07:04.133
To be honest, I don't know
who owns this house.

07:04.600 --> 07:06.035
It's part of a trust.

07:06.101 --> 07:07.636
Two hundred acres of land.

07:08.204 --> 07:09.848
Everything was done
through an intermediary.

07:09.872 --> 07:12.107
They specifically asked me
to handle the listing.

07:14.877 --> 07:17.079
Come on, tub tub.

07:17.346 --> 07:18.614
Hi, baby.

07:19.181 --> 07:20.616
Don't let tub tub loose outside.

07:20.748 --> 07:22.318
There are coyotes here.

07:23.385 --> 07:24.585
Oh, can I pick my own bedroom?

07:24.787 --> 07:26.322
Sure. They're upstairs.

07:26.655 --> 07:28.290
What now?

07:33.295 --> 07:35.864
I need to set up the camera
for the virtual tour.

07:36.764 --> 07:38.167
Sorry about the floor.

07:56.751 --> 08:00.256
Jesus Christ.

08:01.857 --> 08:05.060
I could use a drink.

08:11.033 --> 08:13.235
There's a store
about 20 miles up the road.

08:13.302 --> 08:14.336
I saw a sign.

08:18.807 --> 08:21.110
We can get groceries and wine.

08:22.011 --> 08:24.813
I was thinking of cooking
veal cutlets tonight.

08:26.448 --> 08:28.083
Or I could grill burgers.

08:29.451 --> 08:31.020
Anna and I hate veal.

08:36.358 --> 08:39.928
Great.

08:40.663 --> 08:42.298
Veal cutlets it is.

08:48.237 --> 08:49.571
You know,
just 'cause I messed up,

08:49.638 --> 08:50.639
don't be spiteful.

08:50.739 --> 08:51.840
Oh.

08:52.574 --> 08:54.076
I'm being spiteful?

09:01.150 --> 09:03.352
I really don't know
what the rules are anymore.

09:10.159 --> 09:12.061
Well, it was your idea
to come here.

09:12.695 --> 09:13.595
And you're lucky

09:13.662 --> 09:14.939
because the other
option's divorce

09:14.963 --> 09:17.132
and I don't think that'd
work out too well for you.

09:17.866 --> 09:19.635
Yeah, you would take Anna
and the money.

09:19.935 --> 09:22.971
- I've heard the threats before.
- Then they must be true.

09:26.141 --> 09:27.176
I hate this.

09:29.578 --> 09:30.578
Same.

09:34.083 --> 09:36.418
You know what?
I need a drink too.

09:37.653 --> 09:38.954
Go get food and wine.

09:43.926 --> 09:46.995
Anna, come on.
Mom wants us to run an errand.

09:47.396 --> 09:50.399
- Oh, come on, I'm having fun.
- Yeah, I know.

09:51.533 --> 09:53.869
Yeah, here.

10:04.446 --> 10:05.514
Need a little help.

10:45.921 --> 10:49.124
Wow.

10:53.128 --> 10:55.731
Looks like we're
the city slickers around here.

10:56.031 --> 10:57.733
We're city slickers
everywhere, dad.

11:03.572 --> 11:05.809
- What? You're not gonna help me shop?
- Sorry, dad.

11:06.141 --> 11:07.981
Vintage fashion magazines
are more interesting.

11:08.343 --> 11:09.663
- Oh.
- What do you want me to do?

11:09.813 --> 11:11.313
Okay.

11:47.316 --> 11:48.317
Hey.

11:49.585 --> 11:50.585
What you reading?

11:51.687 --> 11:52.687
Nothing.

11:54.590 --> 11:55.590
Where you from?

11:56.893 --> 11:57.993
Houston.

11:59.595 --> 12:01.129
Wow. That far?

12:05.200 --> 12:06.568
My name's Isaac.

12:09.638 --> 12:10.638
I'm Anna.

12:12.508 --> 12:13.242
You know what, Anna?

12:13.342 --> 12:15.344
You look a lot
like my ex-girlfriend.

12:16.880 --> 12:18.413
- I do?
- Yeah.

12:19.081 --> 12:20.315
Way cuter, though.

12:24.586 --> 12:26.121
Where are you
and your dad staying?

12:26.255 --> 12:27.456
I saw you come in with him.

12:27.924 --> 12:29.258
My mom's here with us too.

12:30.860 --> 12:32.127
They're not getting along.

12:33.462 --> 12:34.462
They mean to you?

12:34.831 --> 12:36.198
No. They're fine.

12:37.366 --> 12:41.503
Um. We're staying at this big,
old house on the water

12:41.804 --> 12:43.105
in the middle of nowhere.

12:44.239 --> 12:46.809
I think I know it.
Uh. About 20 miles east?

12:47.676 --> 12:51.246
Yeah, I think so. My dad drove.

12:51.981 --> 12:53.148
So...

12:54.650 --> 12:55.650
How old are you?

12:56.618 --> 12:57.619
I'm almost 15.

12:58.955 --> 13:01.490
Really? You look a lot older.

13:09.398 --> 13:11.099
We should get
some ice cream sometime.

13:12.501 --> 13:14.369
I'm 18. I'll drive.

13:30.019 --> 13:31.753
- Who were you talking to?
- Hmm?

13:31.854 --> 13:33.322
You making friends over there?

13:33.823 --> 13:34.857
Shut up.

13:38.027 --> 13:40.262
- Register's broken.
- Uh-huh.

13:43.599 --> 13:44.766
Hey.

13:45.400 --> 13:46.879
You wanna help me
bag these things up?

13:46.903 --> 13:47.903
Yeah.

13:50.205 --> 13:52.174
You know, your mom said
you'd like it here.

13:52.774 --> 13:54.576
Didn't she also say to get veal?

13:55.210 --> 13:56.578
Well, they didn't have any.

14:01.249 --> 14:03.318
Oh, look at this.

14:04.419 --> 14:05.419
Pop rocks.

14:05.721 --> 14:06.721
Those are nasty.

14:06.956 --> 14:08.801
What are you talking about?
You used to love these things.

14:08.825 --> 14:10.525
Yeah, when I was like ten.

14:11.460 --> 14:12.900
- Come on, dad.
- Hey, you know what?

14:13.695 --> 14:14.695
Add those.

14:15.631 --> 14:16.631
All right.

14:17.265 --> 14:19.836
Comes to 58 dollars
and six cents.

14:21.436 --> 14:22.604
That is 60.

14:23.605 --> 14:24.605
Keep the change.

14:28.477 --> 14:29.477
Thank you.

14:30.178 --> 14:31.580
Oh, here, you got it.

14:41.223 --> 14:42.391
Dad, you okay?

14:46.996 --> 14:48.163
Um.

14:50.332 --> 14:52.300
Did that old guy
seem odd to you?

14:53.335 --> 14:54.804
No, I don't think so. Why?

14:55.671 --> 14:58.340
Maybe there's somewhere
closer to the house we can shop.

14:58.507 --> 15:00.375
Oh, I don't mind
if we have to come back here.

15:21.898 --> 15:23.565
- Dad.
- Yeah?

15:23.632 --> 15:26.201
- I got a weird question.
- Shoot.

15:28.203 --> 15:30.372
Is everything okay
with you and mom?

15:32.008 --> 15:33.375
Okay in what way?

15:33.775 --> 15:34.844
Don't do that.

15:35.011 --> 15:36.311
- Don't...
- Don't deflect.

15:36.378 --> 15:39.414
That's what mom does.
Can you just be honest?

15:41.184 --> 15:42.584
Marriage is really hard work.

15:42.718 --> 15:45.822
And sometimes, it doesn't go
in the direction you hoped.

15:47.723 --> 15:49.624
- Are you guys getting a divorce?
- No.

15:49.725 --> 15:51.593
- No. No, no, no.
- Don't have to freak out.

15:51.760 --> 15:53.695
- It's fine. I don't care.
- Who's freaking out?

15:53.762 --> 15:56.199
It's just, like, all my friends'
parents are divorced.

15:56.264 --> 15:57.308
- Listen.
- It's not a big deal.

15:57.332 --> 15:59.434
- I...
- Let's not think like that, okay?

15:59.802 --> 16:00.502
Well...

16:00.702 --> 16:03.405
I love you both.

16:04.140 --> 16:06.175
- I just want you to know.
- Good.

16:06.775 --> 16:08.744
You know,
sometimes I think to myself,

16:09.078 --> 16:11.214
"how did I get
such a wise daughter?"

16:11.646 --> 16:13.615
And then I think,

16:14.217 --> 16:16.551
"wow, she probably has
a really wise dad."

16:16.853 --> 16:18.587
Oh, I don't know about that.

16:18.921 --> 16:20.255
Get out.

16:27.529 --> 16:29.165
Maybe Toby needs a friend.

16:29.464 --> 16:30.632
That'd be awesome.

16:34.103 --> 16:36.005
- Mom?
- Jess?

16:36.072 --> 16:38.107
Mom?

16:38.207 --> 16:41.676
Jess?

16:45.514 --> 16:46.748
Mom?

16:47.216 --> 16:49.185
This... this fucking thing
won't open.

16:49.351 --> 16:50.352
Language.

16:50.719 --> 16:52.587
- Door won't open?
- No, a manhole cover

16:52.654 --> 16:54.623
in lower Manhattan.
Yes, the door.

16:56.458 --> 16:58.795
I have to get inside
for the virtual tour.

16:58.995 --> 17:00.129
But don't you have a key?

17:00.362 --> 17:02.731
Yeah, to the house,
the... the pool shed,

17:02.799 --> 17:04.533
the mailbox,
but not for this door.

17:04.666 --> 17:05.868
Jess, let... let me help.

17:05.935 --> 17:06.935
Let me give it a shot.

17:12.208 --> 17:13.843
Okay.

17:23.252 --> 17:25.087
Yeah, that thing's not opening.

17:25.520 --> 17:27.322
- Yeah.
- Do you want me to kick it down?

17:27.622 --> 17:30.325
Hmm. Not yet.

17:31.127 --> 17:32.127
Did you get the veal?

17:33.095 --> 17:34.130
They didn't have any.

17:34.362 --> 17:35.898
So, what did you get instead?

17:36.531 --> 17:39.434
Burger meat for grilling.

17:40.535 --> 17:41.770
Let me see something.

17:50.112 --> 17:51.546
No sunlight gets in.

17:52.281 --> 17:53.415
That's weird.

17:58.054 --> 18:00.388
This room
wasn't on the blueprint.

18:01.356 --> 18:04.392
I... I think it's,
like, a storage room

18:04.459 --> 18:07.662
or maybe a... a panic room.

18:10.032 --> 18:11.766
Freaky.

18:15.905 --> 18:17.372
I'll get it.

18:30.286 --> 18:31.286
Can I help you?

18:31.320 --> 18:32.654
Yeah. So you're Anna's mom.

18:33.789 --> 18:34.789
Who's asking?

18:34.824 --> 18:36.691
Oh, I'm Isaac.
I'm... I'm a friend.

18:37.260 --> 18:38.294
A friend of Anna's?

18:38.895 --> 18:41.063
I met her at my grandpappy's
grocery store today.

18:41.130 --> 18:42.530
Uh-huh. And?

18:42.832 --> 18:44.766
Well, I was just stopping
to invite you

18:44.834 --> 18:46.836
and your family to dinner.

18:46.903 --> 18:49.205
We're your nearest neighbors,
just a few miles that way.

18:49.604 --> 18:51.473
That's very sweet of you, Isaac.

18:51.539 --> 18:52.674
Um.

18:53.109 --> 18:54.509
I'm sorry, we have other plans.

18:54.777 --> 18:57.579
We're on a family vacation.
I'm sure you understand.

18:57.646 --> 19:00.415
I do. I do.
But if you change your mind,

19:00.615 --> 19:01.793
we're having
veal cutlets tonight.

19:01.817 --> 19:03.185
We got a lot in at the store.

19:04.353 --> 19:06.923
Veal cutlets, at your store?

19:07.023 --> 19:07.722
Yes, ma'am.

19:07.957 --> 19:09.557
W... we got a huge
shipment in yesterday.

19:09.825 --> 19:11.827
They're on display.
No one could miss 'em.

19:14.763 --> 19:16.365
Give me your address, Isaac.

19:16.765 --> 19:19.567
On second thought,
we would love to join you.

19:48.763 --> 19:49.899
<i>I'm telling you,</i>

19:50.232 --> 19:51.334
I didn't see it.

19:51.867 --> 19:55.104
Or maybe he's lying
about the stupid cutlets.

19:55.470 --> 19:57.239
He's not lying. You are.

19:57.807 --> 20:00.176
Why would you trust
some stranger over me?

20:02.477 --> 20:04.080
I didn't wanna say anything...

20:06.315 --> 20:07.917
But the old man at the store...

20:09.684 --> 20:11.686
- He wrote this on my receipt.
- Hmm.

20:12.922 --> 20:14.857
"You're being watched
by the devil."

20:16.826 --> 20:19.594
- He's probably making a joke or...
- I don't wanna have dinner

20:19.661 --> 20:22.264
with some creepy locals
just so you can prove a point.

20:22.431 --> 20:23.698
Well... neither do I.

20:23.765 --> 20:25.835
Okay, then.
Would you knock this stuff off?

20:25.901 --> 20:28.904
- Come on. You are beautiful.
- What is wrong with you?

20:30.039 --> 20:31.719
Why couldn't you buy
the veal like I asked?

20:31.773 --> 20:34.576
- I am telling you, I didn't see it.
- Sure you did.

20:34.676 --> 20:37.013
But you hate veal,
so you didn't buy it.

20:37.079 --> 20:39.015
Because you do
exactly what you want

20:39.081 --> 20:40.648
and damn the consequences.

20:41.917 --> 20:43.853
You're not just
talking about veal.

20:44.120 --> 20:46.055
Wow, what a genius you are.

20:50.259 --> 20:53.561
You know, Anna hates veal too.

20:54.629 --> 20:56.332
But you never think about her.

20:56.698 --> 20:59.402
She's all I think about.

20:59.468 --> 21:00.469
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

21:00.735 --> 21:03.172
I think she would be
very surprised to hear that.

21:03.472 --> 21:05.573
So, now, I'm a bad parent?
Not you?

21:05.740 --> 21:08.177
N... not the cheater.
Never you. No, no, no.

21:09.577 --> 21:12.048
You're the nice one
and I'm the asshole.

21:12.448 --> 21:13.482
Isn't that right?

21:14.050 --> 21:15.951
Isn't that how
you try to manipulate Anna

21:16.018 --> 21:17.286
into seeing us?

21:17.787 --> 21:20.356
I'm not gonna stay here
and get emotionally abused.

21:20.588 --> 21:21.756
Then go to your whore.

21:22.024 --> 21:23.926
You know, at least
she made me feel good

21:23.993 --> 21:24.993
about myself.

21:25.094 --> 21:27.662
You make me feel
like slitting my wrists.

21:31.566 --> 21:33.335
Then fucking do it.

21:34.736 --> 21:38.706
You... broke my heart.

21:38.773 --> 21:41.143
Oh, my god.

21:51.287 --> 21:55.657
I loved you. I love you.

21:56.559 --> 21:59.061
- I'm your wife.
- I know.

22:00.429 --> 22:01.763
How could you
treat me like this?

22:01.831 --> 22:04.133
How can you do this to us?

22:04.400 --> 22:05.667
You're right. I am sorry.

22:05.733 --> 22:07.403
I don't know
what's wrong with me.

22:09.905 --> 22:11.673
Did you end things
with that woman?

22:11.807 --> 22:14.276
Yes. It's over
between me and Vivienne.

22:15.144 --> 22:16.879
Do you swear it?

22:18.147 --> 22:19.647
On Anna's life.

22:21.317 --> 22:22.852
Because this is why...

22:23.751 --> 22:26.021
- I brought us here.
- I...

22:26.621 --> 22:28.958
I didn't want you
to sneak off to go see her.

22:29.024 --> 22:33.963
I... I wanted you to give us
a chance to rebuild.

22:34.230 --> 22:35.264
I'm gonna get help.

22:37.500 --> 22:40.402
I just... oh, my god.

22:41.470 --> 22:43.038
It's hard to trust you.

22:43.638 --> 22:47.510
You just keep hurting me...
Over and over.

22:47.610 --> 22:49.145
I'm so sorry.

22:50.045 --> 22:52.281
I want things to be
like they used to.

22:52.348 --> 22:53.382
Mm-hmm.

22:54.649 --> 22:56.085
We're gonna be okay.

22:57.386 --> 22:58.387
We're gonna be okay.

23:21.343 --> 23:23.212
Mom! Dad!

23:25.447 --> 23:26.582
Wow.

23:26.681 --> 23:27.950
- Are you okay, hon?
- Yeah.

23:28.017 --> 23:29.952
I think it's finally stopping.

23:30.920 --> 23:33.422
You know, it happens
when she gets stressed.

23:33.989 --> 23:36.724
How do I look?

23:37.526 --> 23:40.629
Like a supermodel who
got punched in the nose.

23:41.564 --> 23:43.532
At least we have a reason
to stay home tonight.

23:43.899 --> 23:47.145
- Yeah, well, that boy didn't give me a number to call and cancel.
- His name is Isaac.

23:47.169 --> 23:49.572
- Who cares if we don't call and cancel?
- His name's Isaac.

23:50.172 --> 23:51.640
We can't just stand him...

23:51.706 --> 23:52.746
And his grandfather up,

23:52.808 --> 23:54.248
especially if they're
cooking a meal.

23:54.543 --> 23:57.780
- Okay, well...
- Like, what if they mess with the house when we leave?

23:58.080 --> 24:00.983
I'll go to the store
in the morning and apologize.

24:02.785 --> 24:04.863
I don't want Isaac to see me
with a bloody nose, mom.

24:04.887 --> 24:07.189
- I know, honey.
- What if it happens again?

24:09.124 --> 24:11.460
- Okay.
- We can have a nice dinner.

24:12.727 --> 24:14.063
Just the three of us.

24:19.235 --> 24:20.869
Oh. One minute!

24:38.954 --> 24:40.356
Hi there, Anna's mom and dad.

24:40.789 --> 24:42.791
- What are you doing here?
- I'm real sorry.

24:42.858 --> 24:44.603
I... I know you were supposed
to come to our place,

24:44.627 --> 24:46.195
but the strangest
thing happened.

24:46.295 --> 24:48.063
- What's that?
- Our oven died.

24:48.931 --> 24:50.833
- Seriously?
- Yeah. So,

24:51.100 --> 24:52.334
we did the next best thing.

24:52.601 --> 24:54.601
We just brought the food
over here to cook for you.

24:55.170 --> 24:57.273
It's... it's in the truck
with my grandpappy.

24:57.373 --> 24:58.373
Hmm.

24:58.474 --> 25:02.478
Uh. Veal cutlets,
onions, carrots, grits.

25:02.878 --> 25:04.513
Grandpappy sure can cook.

25:05.047 --> 25:06.915
Uh. We even brought
a bottle of wine.

25:08.417 --> 25:10.419
It... it's just how
we do things on the bayou.

25:12.121 --> 25:13.722
- Hmm.
- So, can we come in?

25:13.989 --> 25:15.958
Uh. We'll even do dishes.

25:17.860 --> 25:20.529
Ye... yes,
uh, of course you can.

25:21.096 --> 25:23.699
Hey, grandpappy,
they said it's okay to come in!

25:28.404 --> 25:29.404
Great.

25:29.538 --> 25:30.538
Come on in.

25:52.428 --> 25:53.428
Thanks for cooking.

25:53.696 --> 25:55.030
It's no big deal.

25:57.199 --> 25:58.199
My name's John.

26:01.870 --> 26:03.672
You know,
about that note you wrote me,

26:03.772 --> 26:05.140
the one on the receipt.

26:05.674 --> 26:06.674
I remember.

26:07.943 --> 26:09.211
What did you mean by that?

26:11.914 --> 26:13.916
Get me a measuring cup.

26:19.988 --> 26:21.156
The little one.

26:25.361 --> 26:26.462
Sometimes...

26:27.863 --> 26:31.900
When a man does bad things,
it opens up a door.

26:32.534 --> 26:33.602
I don't understand.

26:34.370 --> 26:35.370
Are you sure?

26:39.007 --> 26:41.477
The devil is watching us
all the time.

26:42.745 --> 26:44.413
Some of us invite him in.

26:45.314 --> 26:46.314
Some don't.

26:47.116 --> 26:49.485
I felt you needed
to hear those words, but...

26:51.286 --> 26:53.389
Didn't want to say 'em
in front of your daughter.

26:55.190 --> 26:57.393
Well, no offense, but I don't
believe in the devil.

27:01.196 --> 27:02.898
The devil believes in you.

27:04.600 --> 27:07.035
Thanks. I appreciate that.

27:20.983 --> 27:22.050
His name's Toby.

27:22.251 --> 27:24.653
We call him tub tub.
He likes you.

27:25.320 --> 27:27.289
Cats can sense things
people can't.

27:31.527 --> 27:34.363
Come on, tub tub.
Yeah, there you go.

27:37.733 --> 27:39.067
Is that thing on?

27:40.502 --> 27:41.502
No.

27:42.938 --> 27:44.808
So, you were saying
it's just you

27:44.874 --> 27:46.408
and your grandfather out here?

27:46.876 --> 27:49.678
Yes, ma'am.
My parents died some time ago.

27:49.813 --> 27:51.213
He raised me as his own.

27:52.181 --> 27:54.149
- How'd your parents die?
- Anna.

27:54.516 --> 27:55.684
Don't. It's rude.

27:56.051 --> 27:58.654
It's fine.
I would be curious too.

27:59.054 --> 28:00.556
Uh. They died of bone cancer.

28:01.723 --> 28:03.425
- Both of them?
- Yes, ma'am.

28:04.226 --> 28:06.762
Grandpappy says bone cancer's
the most painful way to die.

28:07.429 --> 28:10.165
But he says
a lot of crazy things.

28:10.532 --> 28:11.567
He's a wild one.

28:13.135 --> 28:15.637
What are the schools
like around here?

28:16.371 --> 28:18.207
Why? Are you wanting
to move here with Anna?

28:18.740 --> 28:19.740
No.

28:20.275 --> 28:22.211
I wouldn't
know much about schools.

28:23.045 --> 28:24.781
Grandpappy taught me
everything I know.

28:25.314 --> 28:26.783
But I'm gonna run
the store one day.

28:27.115 --> 28:28.283
That's so cool.

28:28.818 --> 28:29.985
You really think so?

28:30.986 --> 28:31.986
Yeah.

28:32.221 --> 28:34.490
I... I like your shirt.
It matches your eyes.

28:34.756 --> 28:35.991
How old are you, Isaac?

28:36.525 --> 28:39.194
Eighteen. I'm trying
to grow a beard.

28:39.261 --> 28:40.529
Hmm.

28:42.364 --> 28:44.166
Who owns this house?
Do you know?

28:45.467 --> 28:48.370
I don't know much about 'em.
They're never really here.

28:48.737 --> 28:49.737
Really?

28:51.206 --> 28:53.475
But being your closest neighbor,
I'd think you'd know.

28:54.510 --> 28:57.079
Hey, everybody,
dinner is almost ready

28:57.145 --> 28:58.680
and it looks delicious.

29:07.589 --> 29:08.589
This is great.

29:10.292 --> 29:11.727
You are one hell of a cook.

29:14.263 --> 29:16.064
There's nothing
my grandpappy can't do.

29:17.399 --> 29:19.167
I bet your mom's
a hell of a cook too.

29:22.304 --> 29:23.304
Um.

29:24.807 --> 29:26.876
- She's, uh...
- No. That's okay, sweetie.

29:26.943 --> 29:30.013
Uh. Cooking isn't my forte.

29:30.078 --> 29:32.481
It's just,
I never got interested in it.

29:32.982 --> 29:35.217
Out here,
cooking isn't an interest.

29:36.685 --> 29:37.719
It's a necessity.

29:40.489 --> 29:42.157
We don't have
restaurants for miles.

29:42.859 --> 29:44.526
You don't cook, you don't eat.

29:45.627 --> 29:48.363
I know how to cook, Isaac.
It's just, uh,

29:48.730 --> 29:50.165
not a passion of mine.

29:51.567 --> 29:52.567
Hmm.

29:53.101 --> 29:54.536
Everyone's got their passion.

30:00.509 --> 30:02.244
Would you mind
if I light some candles?

30:02.711 --> 30:04.546
No, uh...

30:06.748 --> 30:07.749
That would be nice.

30:26.101 --> 30:28.071
- Isaac.
- Yes, ma'am.

30:28.570 --> 30:30.405
How did you know
where the candles are?

30:31.841 --> 30:34.142
Lucky guess.

30:34.710 --> 30:35.710
I'll be.

30:36.211 --> 30:37.221
I guess cats
aren't the only ones

30:37.245 --> 30:38.380
who can sense things.

30:49.491 --> 30:52.327
Pretty funny thing to say, huh, grandpappy?

30:58.901 --> 31:00.268
Gosh, you know...

31:01.938 --> 31:04.139
Uh, I don't have any matches.

31:05.108 --> 31:06.174
Oh, um...

31:06.541 --> 31:08.176
I'll find some
in the kitchen.

31:08.276 --> 31:10.612
John, come help me look.

31:20.089 --> 31:21.529
I want these people
out of the house.

31:21.723 --> 31:23.358
Look. Listen, they're weird,

31:23.425 --> 31:25.260
but they haven't done
anything wrong exactly.

31:25.327 --> 31:27.629
That creepy boy is looking
at Anna in a way I don't like.

31:27.729 --> 31:29.574
- Right.
- And how did he know where the candles are?

31:29.598 --> 31:31.199
Okay, listen,
we will finish dinner

31:31.266 --> 31:33.102
and then we will tell them
we're going to bed.

31:33.168 --> 31:34.328
Can't we get them out faster?

31:34.603 --> 31:36.843
Hey, you're the one that said
we shouldn't piss them off.

31:38.273 --> 31:39.474
Fine.

31:39.641 --> 31:42.711
I... I want them gone
the minute we finish eating.

31:43.245 --> 31:44.881
I don't want Anna
alone with them.

31:45.580 --> 31:47.784
Oh, shit, uh,
we forgot the matches.

31:47.884 --> 31:49.884
Here, come on. I'll tell
them we couldn't find 'em.

31:51.921 --> 31:54.322
Mom, dad, Isaac just did
something really cool.

31:54.857 --> 31:57.759
- What, he found matches?
- No, he touched the candles with his finger

31:57.827 --> 32:00.362
and they just lit up.
Can you do that trick again?

32:00.462 --> 32:02.965
Oh, I'll show you
a lot more tricks, Anna.

32:06.368 --> 32:09.204
Isaac, um,
John and I were talking

32:09.271 --> 32:12.708
and we're grateful for the meal,

32:13.076 --> 32:15.243
but we're really tired
after the drive

32:15.310 --> 32:18.447
and we're going to bed early,
right after dinner.

32:18.714 --> 32:21.249
And I... I just wanted you
and your grandpa to know.

32:21.583 --> 32:24.352
Wow, grandpappy. You hear that?

32:24.519 --> 32:26.055
They're inviting us
to stay the night.

32:26.155 --> 32:28.157
- No, I... I... I...
- We're touched, ma'am.

32:28.623 --> 32:31.760
No one's ever invited us to stay
in a house like this before.

32:34.663 --> 32:37.834
I... I'm not inviting you
to stay the night. I'm...

32:38.935 --> 32:41.703
I'm saying that
you have to leave after dinner,

32:42.604 --> 32:43.705
if not sooner.

32:44.673 --> 32:46.441
But we brought
ice cream for dessert.

32:47.076 --> 32:48.710
Well, we'll eat it
when you're gone.

32:52.115 --> 32:53.115
Oh, come on.

32:53.749 --> 32:54.749
What did we do?

32:55.517 --> 32:57.820
I know there's enough room
in this house for all of us.

32:58.121 --> 33:00.123
Six bedrooms,
if I'm not mistaken.

33:00.622 --> 33:02.390
That's not counting
the game room

33:03.059 --> 33:04.292
or the bonus room...

33:05.560 --> 33:07.763
Or even that locked room
you can't get into.

33:08.663 --> 33:10.298
How do you know
about the locked room?

33:10.732 --> 33:12.101
How do you think?

33:12.334 --> 33:13.903
You've been
in this house before.

33:14.469 --> 33:16.505
Oh, girl, you got a gusher.

33:19.008 --> 33:20.542
Mom, I don't feel good.

33:22.178 --> 33:24.046
- Oh!
- Oh, my god.

33:24.346 --> 33:27.516
- Whoa. Come on. Anna, Anna.
- Oh. Get her.

33:28.251 --> 33:29.852
Oh, for Christ sakes.

33:30.086 --> 33:31.620
I gotta use your pisser.

33:33.321 --> 33:35.024
- Anna.
- Hey, baby?

33:35.557 --> 33:37.994
- Let's get her in the living room, okay?
- Okay.

33:41.696 --> 33:42.799
Anna.

33:43.365 --> 33:46.701
- Wake up. Wake up.
- Wake up. Wake up. Hey.

33:47.170 --> 33:48.170
Hey.

33:49.138 --> 33:51.773
Hey, are you okay? Are you okay?

33:54.743 --> 33:55.743
Hey, sweetie.

33:56.212 --> 33:58.014
- Can you hear my voice?
- Can you hear me?

33:58.080 --> 34:00.749
- Your mom's here. I'm here.
- You're okay.

34:01.884 --> 34:02.884
Mom.

34:04.987 --> 34:06.388
What happ... what happened?

34:06.588 --> 34:09.391
You fainted.
You had another nosebleed.

34:14.297 --> 34:15.530
I have to wash my face.

34:15.798 --> 34:17.934
Oh, it's fine.
I've seen blood before.

34:18.333 --> 34:20.236
- Much more than that.
- You need to leave.

34:20.602 --> 34:21.922
I'm not sure
you want that, ma'am.

34:22.071 --> 34:25.007
She's very sure.
Our daughter isn't feeling well.

34:25.074 --> 34:26.142
Dad, I'm fine.

34:26.242 --> 34:27.552
- No, hey. Isaac...
- No, you're not.

34:27.576 --> 34:29.444
Enough is enough. Come on.

34:31.713 --> 34:33.282
It can take
grandpappy a little bit.

34:33.348 --> 34:34.951
Sometimes he gets the squirts.

34:35.151 --> 34:37.153
- Then go wait in the truck.
- Mom.

34:37.452 --> 34:38.653
- It's okay.
- Wow.

34:39.789 --> 34:42.457
I feel like your cat's
the only one that likes me here.

34:44.126 --> 34:45.560
You cook veal cutlets
for strangers

34:45.627 --> 34:47.063
and this is the thanks you get?

34:49.232 --> 34:51.499
You like me though,
don't you, Anna?

34:52.367 --> 34:53.468
I can tell.

34:55.104 --> 34:57.139
- The way a woman likes a man.
- Stop it!

34:57.372 --> 34:59.175
You're done here,
Isaac. Get out.

34:59.242 --> 35:01.878
I knew you'd have problems
getting into that locked room.

35:02.912 --> 35:03.913
It's the only key.

35:10.485 --> 35:12.955
I think my grandpappy's
tangling with your cat.

35:13.222 --> 35:14.422
Toby?

35:15.523 --> 35:17.226
Wait. Wait.

35:17.293 --> 35:18.794
Toby.

35:21.463 --> 35:23.423
- Toby! Toby!
- What the hell is going on in here?

35:23.531 --> 35:24.651
- Did you hurt our cat?
- No!

35:24.967 --> 35:26.233
- Open the door.
- I was just looking for the bathroom.

35:26.235 --> 35:27.355
- That door was open.
- Toby!

35:27.402 --> 35:29.372
- The cat ran inside.
- Toby.

35:30.006 --> 35:32.942
Now, I may have
closed it by accident.

35:33.209 --> 35:35.410
You're lying. This door
has been locked the entire time.

35:35.778 --> 35:37.646
Grandpappy never lies.

35:37.746 --> 35:41.150
- Toby. Toby.
- Wait, you have a key to the room too?

35:42.318 --> 35:44.353
Toby, Toby, Toby!

35:44.419 --> 35:45.754
Give me the key.

35:46.022 --> 35:47.022
Give it to me.

35:47.422 --> 35:48.982
- Toby! Toby!
- Give me the fucking key!

35:49.025 --> 35:50.159
- This key?
- Yeah!

35:50.393 --> 35:51.553
- Just give it to me.
- Jesus.

35:51.693 --> 35:54.931
Grandpappy, he's hurting me.

35:59.302 --> 36:00.502
See, John?

36:00.803 --> 36:02.504
- Told you I'd show you some tricks.
- Huh?

36:02.737 --> 36:05.007
What's going on?

36:08.443 --> 36:09.845
Good thing we have candles.

36:14.383 --> 36:16.218
Anna, honey, are you okay?

36:16.551 --> 36:18.453
Take your grandson
and get out of here.

36:18.553 --> 36:20.356
- He's not my grandson.
- What?

36:20.689 --> 36:22.425
What do you mean, he's not your grandson?

36:22.490 --> 36:24.592
I mean, he's not my grandson.

36:24.659 --> 36:25.895
All right.

36:25.962 --> 36:27.638
All right, you know what?
Just give me the key.

36:27.662 --> 36:29.822
We're gonna take our cat
and I'm gonna call the police.

36:31.200 --> 36:32.576
- Something's hurting Toby, dad!
- Okay, calm down.

36:32.600 --> 36:33.711
- Something's hurting him!
- Calm down.

36:33.735 --> 36:34.937
Do something, dad.

36:35.004 --> 36:37.306
Can't just open it up.

36:37.440 --> 36:39.275
Toby.

36:39.474 --> 36:41.277
Oh, my god.

36:49.819 --> 36:51.988
Is Toby dead?

36:52.487 --> 36:54.756
Listen, give me the key!

36:55.657 --> 36:56.959
Check your back pocket.

36:58.995 --> 37:00.196
Jesus Christ.

37:04.100 --> 37:05.100
I'll be.

37:05.600 --> 37:07.280
- I'm opening it.
- No, no, no. Stop, stop!

37:07.336 --> 37:08.902
- John, John, John, please. You have to stop.
- I'm opening the door.

37:08.904 --> 37:10.048
- Please stop. We heard...
- I'm opening the door.

37:10.072 --> 37:11.673
- There's something in there.
- Mom,

37:11.740 --> 37:13.517
- Toby's in there!
- There is something... I know,

37:13.541 --> 37:14.981
but there
is something else in there.

37:15.044 --> 37:16.721
- We all heard it. Please don't...
- Could be a coyote went in there,

37:16.745 --> 37:18.280
you know, when the door opened.

37:18.580 --> 37:19.815
Oh, coyote.

37:19.915 --> 37:21.784
Now, that is bad news
for tub tub.

37:21.884 --> 37:23.452
No, no. Enough's enough!

37:23.518 --> 37:25.587
- I'm opening the damn door!
- No, please don't!

37:25.653 --> 37:26.932
- Don't open the door.
- Back off!

37:26.956 --> 37:28.800
Are you out of your mind?
Please, John, let's...

37:28.824 --> 37:30.059
- Come on!
- Let us go.

37:30.192 --> 37:32.004
- Let's go.
- Open the door. Dad, open the door.

37:32.028 --> 37:33.996
Damn, I must have brought
the wrong key.

37:36.765 --> 37:37.800
Can we go, please?

37:38.467 --> 37:41.804
- Can we go? Oh, my god.
- Mom, we can't go! We can't just leave Toby, mom!

37:42.004 --> 37:43.571
Listen to me. It's a cat.

37:43.638 --> 37:44.940
We will buy another cat.

37:45.007 --> 37:46.308
We will.

37:46.442 --> 37:48.144
Grandpappy,
did you find that bathroom?

37:48.576 --> 37:50.455
- We have to get out of here.
- Yeah. Through there.

37:50.479 --> 37:52.114
Of course. I remember now.

37:53.282 --> 37:54.950
Uh. Sorry about your cat.

37:55.683 --> 37:56.886
Fuck you.

37:59.687 --> 38:02.191
Listen,
you need to come with me.

38:02.391 --> 38:04.659
We need to talk
before Isaac gets back.

38:05.094 --> 38:06.829
Follow me.

38:06.896 --> 38:07.963
Come here. Come here.

38:08.230 --> 38:09.631
We have to go. We have to go.

38:11.867 --> 38:14.203
<i>So, are you robbing us?
Is that what's going on?</i>

38:14.669 --> 38:17.672
You ain't got nothing
we need or want.

38:18.174 --> 38:19.208
Then why are you here?

38:20.376 --> 38:21.609
Like I told him...

38:23.179 --> 38:26.714
When a man does bad things,
it opens up a door.

38:26.849 --> 38:29.085
You are nuts and so is that kid.

38:29.785 --> 38:31.153
Bad things?

38:31.220 --> 38:32.354
Bad things like what?

38:33.456 --> 38:34.589
Like lying.

38:35.357 --> 38:36.357
Cheating.

38:37.493 --> 38:38.493
Murder.

38:38.828 --> 38:40.996
- Ain't you read your <i>Bible?</i>
- Oh, god.

38:42.064 --> 38:44.400
In the store,
Isaac was so nice to me.

38:45.434 --> 38:47.870
He said I looked like his ex-girlfriend.

38:48.804 --> 38:50.339
Now, he's being so mean.

38:50.705 --> 38:52.942
Yeah, well...

38:53.409 --> 38:55.044
That's Isaac in a nutshell.

38:55.978 --> 38:58.180
If Isaac isn't your grandson,

38:58.347 --> 38:59.381
then who is he?

39:00.916 --> 39:04.787
He just
sort of appeared one summer.

39:05.653 --> 39:07.156
Walked right out of the bayou.

39:08.858 --> 39:12.627
Said his parents had died,
left him a bunch of money.

39:15.030 --> 39:18.633
Never even told me
his last name.

39:20.970 --> 39:23.205
But he didn't have
no place to live.

39:24.607 --> 39:26.242
Didn't have no possessions.

39:28.043 --> 39:30.813
So I kinda, sorta, took him in.

39:31.347 --> 39:33.115
- You took him in?
- Stop!

39:34.850 --> 39:36.418
I'm not done talking.

39:42.591 --> 39:44.360
He ain't got no education...

39:45.828 --> 39:47.963
But he's got
a good Christian spirit.

39:51.200 --> 39:55.437
I... I guess
I'm his helpmate, so to speak.

39:55.538 --> 39:56.839
Oh, god.

39:57.573 --> 39:58.908
How long has he lived with you?

39:59.275 --> 40:01.877
It's hard telling.
You lose track of time

40:02.278 --> 40:03.445
out on the bayou.

40:04.246 --> 40:07.349
Few years, maybe.

40:08.617 --> 40:09.652
Maybe decades.

40:09.818 --> 40:11.220
There's no way.

40:13.688 --> 40:14.790
Thing is...

40:16.025 --> 40:18.260
He don't never seem
to get any older.

40:19.895 --> 40:22.264
He's good with those damn
magic tricks, though, isn't he?

40:23.599 --> 40:25.401
But he always looks
the same to me.

40:25.668 --> 40:26.869
Maybe 18 or so.

40:27.069 --> 40:28.703
- This is bullshit.
- Just let him talk.

40:28.804 --> 40:30.406
- No, it's bullshit!
- Let him talk!

40:33.108 --> 40:35.044
I'd like to put some music on.

40:35.911 --> 40:37.880
Make sure Isaac can't hear.

40:39.515 --> 40:41.016
I got something else
to tell you.

41:05.874 --> 41:06.994
<i>So, what are you telling me?</i>

41:07.142 --> 41:08.286
<i>You telling me that
she found out about us?</i>

41:08.310 --> 41:09.310
<i>I wasn't careful enough.</i>

41:09.878 --> 41:12.514
<i>I was so stupid about it.
Yes, she followed me, okay?</i>

41:12.581 --> 41:13.649
<i>I just found out about it.</i>

41:14.083 --> 41:16.328
- <i>She could be watching us right now.</i>
