- Wait, wait.

44:45.994 --> 44:47.095
Who took my phone?

44:47.262 --> 44:50.098
- Where is my phone?
- Stop, dad! Stop!

44:50.165 --> 44:51.165
Maybe it was Vivienne.

44:51.333 --> 44:52.377
Maybe... maybe she's the one
that set you up.

44:52.401 --> 44:53.702
Did you ever think about that?

44:55.370 --> 44:57.773
And you're a lying,
cheating asshole

44:57.907 --> 45:00.576
and she's probably
exactly like you.

45:01.410 --> 45:04.646
You're the one who followed me,
who stalked me.

45:04.948 --> 45:06.883
Exactly. What if she's doing
the same thing?

45:06.982 --> 45:09.418
Please stop!

45:12.789 --> 45:14.256
Before you played that...

45:15.457 --> 45:16.457
Record...

45:18.327 --> 45:19.628
What were you going to say?

45:20.596 --> 45:22.297
I was gonna tell you
that there's something

45:22.364 --> 45:24.533
you need to see
in that locked room.

45:33.075 --> 45:35.544
- Holy shit!
- What?

45:35.812 --> 45:37.012
Someone's out there.

45:38.146 --> 45:39.146
Where?

45:39.381 --> 45:41.450
I saw something by the water.

45:41.818 --> 45:43.018
Could be a coyote.

45:43.452 --> 45:46.555
Yeah, could be. Or maybe a wolf.

45:47.189 --> 45:48.457
Even a wild dog.

45:53.662 --> 45:54.797
There!

45:54.864 --> 45:56.775
- I don't see it. Where are you looking?
- No, I saw it.

45:56.799 --> 45:58.367
I saw it too.

46:00.803 --> 46:03.338
Probably just a coyote.
Or a wolf.

46:04.239 --> 46:05.674
Better to be safe though.

46:13.783 --> 46:15.250
Good thing
this gun's still here.

46:16.351 --> 46:17.351
Whoa.

46:19.087 --> 46:20.222
Don't worry.

46:21.256 --> 46:23.125
If you're righteous,
you'll survive.

46:24.259 --> 46:27.362
- Just be careful, please.
- Wait.

46:27.763 --> 46:28.831
How's this camera work?

46:32.601 --> 46:35.070
<i>Look, grandpappy.</i>

46:36.138 --> 46:37.339
<i>I'm a movie star.</i>

46:39.274 --> 46:41.143
Don't put me on that.

46:42.812 --> 46:43.812
Isaac.

46:45.180 --> 46:46.748
Isaac, what is it that you want?

46:49.151 --> 46:51.353
I want you to take
real good care of this camera.

46:52.521 --> 46:54.857
<i>I'm gonna be famous one day.</i>

46:55.858 --> 46:57.359
<i>Just like Charles manson.</i>

47:07.603 --> 47:10.138
You know,
you hear about god's son.

47:11.740 --> 47:13.208
Does Satan have a son?

47:13.943 --> 47:16.411
Food for thought.

47:21.383 --> 47:22.785
Please put that gun down.

47:24.020 --> 47:25.888
- Let's go outside, John.
- No.

47:28.423 --> 47:31.159
- Why not?
- Because you're gonna shoot me.

47:31.627 --> 47:32.627
Shoot you?

47:33.195 --> 47:36.899
- <i>♪ Tell me the truth... ♪</i>
- I thought we were gonna go hunt coyotes.

47:37.766 --> 47:40.602
We can talk about this.
Can we talk about this, please?

47:41.104 --> 47:42.839
Will you please
put that gun down?

47:43.205 --> 47:45.307
- Please?
- Jessica.

47:46.775 --> 47:47.775
Fine.

47:48.477 --> 47:50.379
I'll leave the gun
with grandpappy.

47:51.279 --> 47:52.581
You can stay here with your wife

47:52.648 --> 47:53.648
and your daughter.

47:55.350 --> 48:00.857
<i>♪ If you will only
tell me the truth ♪</i>

48:01.623 --> 48:03.625
Okay, John. No gun.

48:04.127 --> 48:06.395
- <i>♪ Whoa...</i>
- Let's go for that walk.

48:08.196 --> 48:10.265
- John.
- No, dad. Dad.

48:10.399 --> 48:12.434
Just stay here.
It'll be all right.

48:12.935 --> 48:13.970
- Don't go.
- It's okay.

48:14.037 --> 48:16.438
- Don't go, dad. Don't go.
- I know. I know.

48:16.772 --> 48:17.772
It's okay.

48:20.442 --> 48:25.447
<i>♪ And I just don't understand ♪</i>

48:27.817 --> 48:33.755
<i>♪ why don't you tell me
the truth ♪</i>

48:37.492 --> 48:39.361
Oh, come on, little girlie.

48:40.163 --> 48:41.763
You don't gotta be frightened.

48:43.132 --> 48:44.566
I'm not the bogeyman.

48:46.301 --> 48:51.640
<i>♪ That I'm willing
to let you go ♪</i>

48:52.108 --> 48:53.575
<i>♪ whoa ♪</i>

48:53.843 --> 48:58.815
<i>♪ without your love ♪</i>

49:17.066 --> 49:20.469
This wasn't the deal we made.

49:22.604 --> 49:25.141
No, listen,
all you have to do is Rob us

49:25.340 --> 49:27.009
and shoot Jessica.

49:27.110 --> 49:28.744
What the fuck
are you doing in there?

49:28.811 --> 49:30.579
What the fuck are you
pushing me for?

49:32.815 --> 49:34.917
How did you get that recording
of me and Vivienne?

49:35.051 --> 49:36.685
- Oh, magic.
- Yeah?

49:36.752 --> 49:38.487
- Yeah.
- I have to look squeaky-clean

49:38.553 --> 49:41.157
and you have to be believable
for Anna's sake.

49:41.224 --> 49:42.357
Oh, I'm not believable?

49:42.892 --> 49:46.028
They don't know I'm 21,
that... that I was in the army.

49:46.361 --> 49:48.563
But you keep fucking up my plan.

49:48.931 --> 49:50.066
I'm fucking up?

49:50.599 --> 49:52.734
I'm not the one
trying to murder my wife.

49:52.835 --> 49:53.836
Don't say that.

49:54.302 --> 49:55.805
- Murder? Murder.
- Don't say that.

49:55.872 --> 49:57.381
- Don't say that.
- You don't like that word.

49:57.405 --> 49:59.741
- Murder. Murder.
- Don't say that. Don't say that.

49:59.809 --> 50:02.812
Don't say that.
Don't say that, Isaac.

50:03.645 --> 50:05.313
Get off of me.

50:09.051 --> 50:10.285
This was the perfect plan.

50:10.485 --> 50:11.845
I knew that
she would drag me here.

50:11.888 --> 50:14.489
She babbled
about this stupid house nonstop.

50:14.791 --> 50:17.759
I spent so long strategizing
and finding you.

50:17.827 --> 50:18.827
Yeah.

50:19.494 --> 50:21.998
It's not easy finding a killer for hire.

50:22.297 --> 50:24.133
You gotta visit
some pretty dark places.

50:24.901 --> 50:27.569
I'm not gonna pay you
if this thing goes sideways.

50:27.804 --> 50:28.805
Oh.

50:29.205 --> 50:31.339
Yeah, 'cause you'll be in jail.

50:31.874 --> 50:32.707
Well, so will you.

50:32.875 --> 50:34.519
Along with that crazy, old man
you work with.

50:34.543 --> 50:36.179
He's never
gonna see daylight again.

50:36.545 --> 50:38.680
You're gonna see
the electric chair, bub.

50:40.116 --> 50:41.750
You're the mastermind here.

50:42.819 --> 50:43.953
We're just country folk.

50:44.921 --> 50:47.455
What happened to our cat
in that locked room?

50:48.657 --> 50:51.326
Maybe a coyote killed him
and I brought him back to life.

50:51.393 --> 50:52.570
This is what I'm talking about.

50:52.594 --> 50:54.696
You quit scaring people
with this voodoo shit

50:54.763 --> 50:55.998
and do your job.

50:57.200 --> 50:58.767
This is my job.

50:59.101 --> 51:00.101
Okay.

51:00.702 --> 51:03.538
Keep the train on the tracks
and you'll get your 100 grand.

51:03.605 --> 51:06.275
Then you can take the car
to Mexico, like we planned.

51:06.441 --> 51:08.610
I feel like
you're trying to control me.

51:10.847 --> 51:12.148
You want your wife gone,

51:12.882 --> 51:14.516
you want a good story
for your kid,

51:15.017 --> 51:18.020
for the cops
and your shiny, new girlfriend.

51:19.322 --> 51:20.522
That takes work.

51:21.791 --> 51:23.025
That takes trust.

51:26.494 --> 51:28.663
Are you sure you want
to go through with this?

51:29.531 --> 51:31.968
We can call
this whole thing off right now.

51:32.367 --> 51:33.468
No, we are doing it,

51:33.535 --> 51:35.704
but from now on,
play by the rules.

51:36.371 --> 51:37.639
- Okay.
- Okay.

51:38.406 --> 51:39.909
So go in there,

51:39.976 --> 51:41.911
Rob us,
and when we're walking back

51:41.978 --> 51:45.380
to the locked room,
you shoot Jessica in the head

51:45.480 --> 51:47.116
and then you get the fuck out.

51:49.584 --> 51:50.584
Okay.

52:06.701 --> 52:09.005
They've been gone so long now.

52:11.274 --> 52:14.643
I could put some music on again.

52:14.776 --> 52:15.776
No.

52:16.511 --> 52:17.712
No, it's okay.

52:18.047 --> 52:19.181
What...

52:21.350 --> 52:22.785
What's... what's your real name?

52:25.453 --> 52:26.923
Grandpappy's fine.

52:28.423 --> 52:30.092
Grandpappy. Grandpappy.

52:35.463 --> 52:36.966
I wanna ask you something.

52:37.800 --> 52:38.800
Yeah?

52:42.771 --> 52:44.773
I think there's something
wrong with Isaac.

52:45.674 --> 52:48.244
I think that he is... evil,

52:48.811 --> 52:50.445
and he wants to hurt people.

52:52.214 --> 52:54.116
Yeah, some days,
I think that too.

52:58.020 --> 52:59.956
- But you're not like him.
- Hmm.

53:00.323 --> 53:01.791
Not from what I can tell.

53:05.227 --> 53:06.227
So...

53:09.664 --> 53:11.133
I'd like to make a proposition.

53:12.234 --> 53:13.936
- A proposition?
- Yes.

53:17.206 --> 53:18.673
Let me and my daughter go.

53:19.308 --> 53:20.943
We'll sneak out.
Isaac won't see us.

53:21.010 --> 53:23.779
We'll get in our car
and drive away.

53:24.347 --> 53:25.580
What about dad?

53:25.815 --> 53:26.815
Quiet.

53:31.486 --> 53:32.855
You'll go to the police.

53:32.955 --> 53:34.991
I'll tell them
that you're innocent.

53:35.523 --> 53:37.927
I'll say that you're a hostage
just like us.

53:39.661 --> 53:43.165
But I have a gun.

53:45.567 --> 53:47.769
Well, I think Isaac
is making you do this.

53:48.503 --> 53:49.738
I know he is.

53:51.073 --> 53:54.877
I can't turn my back on him.

53:56.012 --> 53:57.813
If you let us go, I will...

53:57.980 --> 54:00.116
I will give you
everything I have.

54:01.683 --> 54:03.185
Mom, what about dad?

54:04.253 --> 54:05.921
We can't just
leave him here to die.

54:06.422 --> 54:07.522
Hush.

54:08.457 --> 54:09.758
They're almost back.

54:10.793 --> 54:12.594
Oh, shit.

54:14.629 --> 54:16.698
I can't believe
you wanted to leave dad.

54:18.700 --> 54:20.069
Don't tell him I said that.

54:31.313 --> 54:32.714
We didn't see any coyotes.

54:33.115 --> 54:34.216
But we did some talking.

54:35.518 --> 54:38.020
Ma'am, your husband's right.

54:38.454 --> 54:39.454
We're robbing you.

54:40.089 --> 54:42.258
Me and grandpappy
are gonna lock you in that room.

54:42.825 --> 54:44.236
See, we've been sneaking
in this house

54:44.260 --> 54:45.394
for a few weeks now.

54:45.693 --> 54:47.129
Thought you were the new owners.

54:47.662 --> 54:48.998
Just bad luck, really.

54:49.432 --> 54:50.598
Like bone cancer.

54:51.766 --> 54:53.202
You're gonna lock us
in the room?

54:53.536 --> 54:54.536
Yes, ma'am.

54:54.970 --> 54:56.771
After we take
your money and your SUV.

54:56.872 --> 55:01.743
- That was their plan all along.
- But we'll die if you lock us up. How... how will we get out?

55:02.178 --> 55:05.247
We'll call the police,
leave an anonymous tip.

55:05.981 --> 55:08.117
I'll leave some food and
water in there for you.

55:08.184 --> 55:10.319
Thank you. I trust them.

55:10.386 --> 55:12.021
You're a fucking idiot.

55:12.088 --> 55:14.156
They are not
gonna call the police.

55:16.425 --> 55:19.761
My daughter is 14 years old.

55:19.862 --> 55:24.100
Please, i'm... I'm asking you,
please don't do this.

55:24.533 --> 55:27.436
- Ma'am, you have my word.
- Your word?

55:27.735 --> 55:30.039
- Your word doesn't mean anything.
- Calm down, okay?

55:30.106 --> 55:33.209
Your word means even less.
Why the fuck would I calm down?

55:33.342 --> 55:35.710
Jess.

55:36.278 --> 55:37.513
It's the room or a bullet.

55:45.387 --> 55:46.889
It's okay.

56:02.505 --> 56:03.638
Time's wasting.

56:04.639 --> 56:06.142
What is this place?

56:06.609 --> 56:07.775
Why are you doing this?

56:08.344 --> 56:11.514
- Why are you doing this?
- I think we just have to put our differences aside...

56:11.580 --> 56:12.815
And do what they...

56:12.882 --> 56:14.150
Don't talk to me!

56:19.721 --> 56:21.157
You first, John.

56:22.657 --> 56:24.393
Me?

56:25.928 --> 56:27.796
- It's okay.
- Dad.

56:28.597 --> 56:29.798
- Go on.
- No.

56:33.335 --> 56:35.905
- No. No.
- All right.

56:44.213 --> 56:45.213
Dad.

56:47.616 --> 56:49.218
Come on.

57:00.963 --> 57:02.097
Isaac?

57:03.666 --> 57:05.301
Isaac, what are you doing?

57:05.935 --> 57:07.636
I'm putting you
where you belong, John.

57:07.836 --> 57:12.141
Isaac, let me out.

57:12.641 --> 57:13.741
John...

57:15.077 --> 57:16.077
Isaac.

57:16.946 --> 57:19.081
- Let me out.
- Hey, John?

57:20.249 --> 57:21.317
Murder.

57:24.719 --> 57:26.889
Let me out, Isaac.

57:29.158 --> 57:30.326
Isaac...

57:30.758 --> 57:32.161
Isaac...

57:33.028 --> 57:34.063
Isaac...

57:34.663 --> 57:36.599
I'm gonna kill you!

57:37.066 --> 57:39.702
Isaac, open the door!

57:39.868 --> 57:40.903
Open the door!

57:41.203 --> 57:43.305
I'm gonna fucking
tear you apart.

57:47.176 --> 57:48.176
See, ma'am,

57:48.310 --> 57:50.713
I'm guessing he's cheated on you
many a times before

57:50.813 --> 57:52.081
with many different women.

57:52.147 --> 57:53.983
But you always take
him back, don't you?

57:54.049 --> 57:56.027
- What is he talking about?
- I... I... I don't... I don't know.

57:56.051 --> 57:57.086
Anna...

57:57.152 --> 58:00.055
Hey, baby.
Don't listen to Isaac.

58:00.522 --> 58:01.756
Don't listen to him.

58:02.091 --> 58:05.561
Isaac! What do you
think you're doing?

58:05.728 --> 58:07.363
You've been in denial
about your husband

58:07.429 --> 58:08.597
for a long time now.

58:09.231 --> 58:11.231
- Anna! Let me out!
- It's time you face the truth.

58:13.936 --> 58:15.070
Better go get that.

58:15.770 --> 58:17.139
- Don't worry.
- Isaac...

58:17.206 --> 58:19.341
Me and grandpappy will stay
right here with Anna.

58:19.475 --> 58:20.943
No. No.

58:21.176 --> 58:24.647
No, mom, you can't leave me.
No, you can't leave, mom.

58:25.014 --> 58:27.283
- Mom.
- You dirty motherfucker!

58:28.317 --> 58:29.317
Isaac!

58:31.453 --> 58:32.655
Open the door.

58:32.721 --> 58:34.323
Open the door!

58:34.657 --> 58:38.460
Open this fucking door!

58:38.627 --> 58:40.429
Anna? Anna.

58:40.663 --> 58:44.433
Baby, don't listen to what he says, baby.

58:44.867 --> 58:46.235
Listen, he's a liar.

58:46.468 --> 58:51.240
If he says anything about me,
you know he's lying, okay?

58:51.640 --> 58:54.743
Okay? Same with your mother!

58:55.010 --> 58:57.813
Same with your fucking mother!

59:03.752 --> 59:04.920
You.

59:05.321 --> 59:06.321
Oh, my god.

59:07.289 --> 59:08.090
You're his wife.

59:08.290 --> 59:10.726
Oh, my god.
I'm so sorry. I... I got a text.

59:10.893 --> 59:12.828
From my husband?

59:13.262 --> 59:14.262
Yes.

59:14.897 --> 59:16.465
You knew he was married?

59:17.032 --> 59:18.600
You're as bad as he is.

59:18.802 --> 59:20.369
I'm really, really sorry.

59:20.569 --> 59:23.305
I am. He... he told me that
he was here all alone here,

59:23.372 --> 59:25.074
that he needed me
to come right away.

59:25.274 --> 59:27.943
See? I drove as fast as I could.

59:28.977 --> 59:31.480
- My husband didn't text you that.
- What?

59:31.714 --> 59:32.794
This house is being robbed.

59:33.048 --> 59:35.048
The men are still inside.
They have John locked up.

59:35.819 --> 59:37.953
- Are you serious?
- Yes. My daughter's inside too.

59:38.220 --> 59:40.689
They took John's phone
and texted you to lure you here.

59:40.756 --> 59:42.291
- Why?
- To hurt you. They're crazy.

59:42.491 --> 59:45.036
- They have a gun.
- Okay, well... well, I'll help however you need, okay?

59:45.060 --> 59:47.906
- I'll... I'll call the police.
- No, phones don't work. Do you have anything

59:47.930 --> 59:49.833
I can use as a weapon?
I don't know, a knife?

59:49.998 --> 59:51.476
- Mace. Mace.
- Give it to me. Give it to me.

59:51.500 --> 59:53.020
- Okay.
- You need to go to the police.

59:53.068 --> 59:54.828
Tell them that we are
being held at gunpoint.

59:54.870 --> 59:56.572
There's an old man
and a teenage boy.

59:56.638 --> 59:58.640
Is John okay? Anna?

59:59.641 --> 1:00:01.577
Do not use my daughter's name.

1:00:02.812 --> 1:00:04.113
You disgust me.

1:00:04.747 --> 1:00:07.427
- I actually came here to break up with John.
- I don't give a shit.

1:00:07.516 --> 1:00:09.327
- You can have him.
- He told me all of this...

1:00:09.351 --> 1:00:10.351
Shut up.

1:00:12.121 --> 1:00:14.456
From now on,
my family is me and my daughter.

1:00:15.691 --> 1:00:19.261
If you don't come back here
with the police and I survive...

1:00:20.129 --> 1:00:23.499
I swear, I will find you
and I will kill you.

1:00:24.733 --> 1:00:26.034
I'll get help. I swear.

1:00:26.935 --> 1:00:28.270
- Go.
- Okay.

1:00:55.664 --> 1:00:57.299
No, don't do this.

1:00:59.935 --> 1:01:01.336
They're taking too long.

1:01:01.970 --> 1:01:03.605
Take Anna out
and get the gasoline.

1:01:04.239 --> 1:01:05.240
Anna!

1:01:05.340 --> 1:01:06.508
Dad! Dad!

1:01:06.608 --> 1:01:07.376
Anna!

1:01:07.576 --> 1:01:09.745
Isaac, you betrayed me.

1:01:10.179 --> 1:01:12.782
- You betrayed me!
- You betrayed your own family.

1:01:12.849 --> 1:01:14.450
I'm gonna Bury
every cent of that money.

1:01:14.516 --> 1:01:18.654
You're not gonna see anything.
You're not gonna see anything!

1:01:18.954 --> 1:01:20.924
You really think
I was in this for the money?

1:01:22.724 --> 1:01:27.596
Put the key in, Isaac.
Put the key in!

1:01:27.931 --> 1:01:30.432
Put the key in, Isaac!

1:01:30.566 --> 1:01:32.100
Let me out!

1:01:32.167 --> 1:01:34.069
Open the fucking door!

1:01:34.136 --> 1:01:36.271
Isaac. Isaac!

1:01:36.438 --> 1:01:39.007
- Open the door!
- Check the closet, John.

1:01:39.775 --> 1:01:41.176
It's your only way out.

1:02:17.145 --> 1:02:19.147
Open that closet fast, John.

1:02:27.824 --> 1:02:28.824
Come on.

1:02:32.661 --> 1:02:34.730
Shit.

1:02:36.498 --> 1:02:37.699
- Oh, my god.
- Try it again.

1:02:37.766 --> 1:02:39.286
- I'm trying.
- Try it again, Vivienne.

1:02:40.502 --> 1:02:41.804
Okay.

1:02:41.871 --> 1:02:43.105
- Oh, my god.
- Vivienne.

1:02:43.305 --> 1:02:45.040
The doors won't open.

1:02:45.240 --> 1:02:47.209
- What is happening?
- I'm trapped!

1:02:48.310 --> 1:02:49.012
Jessica.

1:02:49.077 --> 1:02:50.646
- Look out.
- Mom.

1:02:51.981 --> 1:02:53.582
Grandpappy's making me do this.

1:03:00.023 --> 1:03:02.391
Stop.

1:03:02.457 --> 1:03:04.726
Right there.

1:03:09.698 --> 1:03:12.601
It's a fine night for a bonfire,
don't you think?

1:03:14.037 --> 1:03:15.203
That's what Isaac says.

1:03:15.337 --> 1:03:16.940
We called the police on you.

1:03:17.573 --> 1:03:20.409
- They're on their way.
- Now, you know that's not true.

1:03:21.911 --> 1:03:23.478
Isaac's controlling this,
isn't he?

1:03:23.913 --> 1:03:24.913
But why?

1:03:25.080 --> 1:03:27.382
Maybe he didn't have
nothing better to do.

1:03:28.550 --> 1:03:31.253
It's so heavy, mom.
I can't hold it anymore.

1:03:32.087 --> 1:03:34.489
You start pouring
that gasoline on the car.

1:03:36.625 --> 1:03:39.328
- There's a woman inside.
- That woman is no good.

1:03:40.095 --> 1:03:42.164
- You know what? Her and your dad...
- Hey.

1:03:42.497 --> 1:03:43.497
Don't say it.

1:03:43.732 --> 1:03:44.732
Why?

1:03:45.001 --> 1:03:46.768
You trying to protect
his good name?

1:03:46.836 --> 1:03:48.303
I'm protecting my daughter.

1:03:49.671 --> 1:03:50.671
Anna...

1:03:52.875 --> 1:03:55.677
Start pouring that gas
or I'm gonna shoot your mama.

1:03:57.346 --> 1:04:00.382
You do it yourself.
You don't make my child do it.

1:04:00.482 --> 1:04:02.085
That's not how this works.

1:04:02.317 --> 1:04:03.452
Don't.

1:04:03.920 --> 1:04:04.921
Don't! Don't!

1:04:05.287 --> 1:04:07.155
- Don't. Stop it, please!
- No. Hey.

1:04:07.857 --> 1:04:08.857
Go back.

1:04:09.658 --> 1:04:10.658
I'll do it.

1:04:10.759 --> 1:04:11.759
- No!
- Good.

1:04:12.929 --> 1:04:13.929
No.

1:04:14.931 --> 1:04:16.498
- Don't!
- Anna, shut your eyes.

1:04:16.632 --> 1:04:17.332
Mom.

1:04:17.633 --> 1:04:19.768
No, Jessica!

1:04:20.469 --> 1:04:22.071
No!

1:04:22.471 --> 1:04:25.540
- Make sure you get some under the hood.
- I'm sorry!

1:04:25.741 --> 1:04:28.978
No, Jessica! Oh, my god!

1:04:29.378 --> 1:04:31.114
No, Jessica, please!

1:04:31.446 --> 1:04:33.715
- Jessica, no!
- I'm so fucking sorry.

1:04:33.783 --> 1:04:36.184
No!

1:04:37.486 --> 1:04:39.287
No!

1:04:44.593 --> 1:04:48.497
Jessica! I'm sorry!
I'm sorry, Jessica!

1:04:48.730 --> 1:04:51.166
Please! Stop!

1:04:52.035 --> 1:04:54.770
Jessica! Please!

1:04:55.038 --> 1:04:56.072
Stop!

1:04:56.139 --> 1:04:58.141
No!

1:04:58.540 --> 1:05:00.877
- Don't do it! No!
- Ashes to ashes.

1:05:02.111 --> 1:05:03.046
Dust to dust.

1:05:03.112 --> 1:05:04.881
No, Jessica!

1:05:05.547 --> 1:05:06.547
Oh, my god!

1:05:11.219 --> 1:05:13.122
Just like cooking veal.

1:05:13.255 --> 1:05:14.589
Oh, my god.

1:05:16.025 --> 1:05:18.727
Please, Jessica, no!

1:05:22.764 --> 1:05:24.801
Help me!

1:05:25.134 --> 1:05:26.635
No!

1:05:28.403 --> 1:05:29.538
No!

1:05:30.405 --> 1:05:33.642
- Anna, run!
- Jessica! No!

1:05:36.678 --> 1:05:39.448
Motherfucker!

1:05:43.152 --> 1:05:44.653
- Anna!
- Mom!

1:05:44.821 --> 1:05:47.656
Oh, god. Vivienne. Vivienne.

1:05:48.791 --> 1:05:49.992
Oh, god, Vivienne.

1:05:51.894 --> 1:05:52.895
Oh, my god!

1:05:53.395 --> 1:05:57.332
Shit. Vivienne! Fuck!

1:06:03.039 --> 1:06:04.941
Honey, no, it's okay.

1:06:05.240 --> 1:06:07.009
Come here, Anna.
Anna, look at me.

1:06:07.176 --> 1:06:10.012
Look at me. Are you okay?
Are you okay? Okay.

1:06:10.412 --> 1:06:13.082
All right. Honey. Oh, god.

1:06:13.381 --> 1:06:16.085
- No keys. Shit, shit, shit.
- Isaac has all the keys.

1:06:16.185 --> 1:06:20.189
Oh, dad has the other key.
Honey, honey, you have to stay.

1:06:20.489 --> 1:06:21.991
- Okay, listen to me.
- What?

1:06:22.058 --> 1:06:23.258
If you see Isaac,

1:06:23.425 --> 1:06:24.693
- you're gonna scream...
- No.

1:06:24.827 --> 1:06:26.270
- And then you shoot him.
- No, no, no.

1:06:26.294 --> 1:06:27.672
- Mom, I can't do this.
- You can do this.

1:06:27.696 --> 1:06:29.999
- You can't... I can't do this.
- You're gonna do this.

1:06:30.066 --> 1:06:31.733
Listen to me. You're gonna aim

1:06:31.868 --> 1:06:33.628
and you're gonna shoot
and I'll come running.

1:06:33.668 --> 1:06:36.371
You're gonna aim at his eyes, okay?

1:06:36.471 --> 1:06:38.406
- Listen to me.
- I can't do this, mom!

1:06:38.473 --> 1:06:39.474
Listen to me.

1:06:40.076 --> 1:06:42.945
If I don't try to save your dad,
you will never forgive me.

1:06:43.012 --> 1:06:45.747
Okay. Okay.

1:06:46.581 --> 1:06:48.050
Mom, what are you gonna do?

1:06:48.217 --> 1:06:49.919
Take this. It's mace.

1:06:50.385 --> 1:06:52.721
I'm gonna find Isaac.

1:07:17.746 --> 1:07:18.781
Isaac?

1:07:23.286 --> 1:07:25.720
Isaac.

1:07:34.496 --> 1:07:36.464
Grandpappy needs you.

1:07:37.934 --> 1:07:39.701
He's hurt real bad.

1:07:54.283 --> 1:07:55.450
John?

1:08:12.301 --> 1:08:14.136
Hello?

1:08:22.979 --> 1:08:26.182
John?

1:08:51.740 --> 1:08:54.210
John?

1:08:54.377 --> 1:08:55.878
John.

1:09:04.220 --> 1:09:05.220
Jess...

1:09:12.228 --> 1:09:15.398
Is Anna okay?

1:09:15.865 --> 1:09:18.667
She's fine.

1:09:18.733 --> 1:09:21.337
Isaac said
that Vivienne is here...

1:09:24.874 --> 1:09:27.176
And they killed her.

1:09:27.243 --> 1:09:28.243
No.

1:09:28.911 --> 1:09:30.745
Vivienne's...

1:09:30.813 --> 1:09:34.050
Vivienne's alive.

1:09:35.351 --> 1:09:38.553
She's... she's waiting for you.

1:09:48.596 --> 1:09:50.532
John, do you have the car keys?

1:09:53.936 --> 1:09:55.237
Isaac took them.

1:09:59.474 --> 1:10:00.775
Jessica...

1:10:02.644 --> 1:10:07.817
Tell Vivienne I love her.

1:10:08.616 --> 1:10:12.587
I will.

1:10:47.957 --> 1:10:48.957
Hey.

1:10:49.492 --> 1:10:50.625
Mom!

1:10:52.361 --> 1:10:53.362
Don't come any closer.

1:10:53.661 --> 1:10:55.965
- Or what?
- Or I'll shoot you.

1:10:57.033 --> 1:10:59.168
Mom, it's Isaac! Mom!

1:11:00.836 --> 1:11:02.604
You ever even shot a gun before?

1:11:04.407 --> 1:11:06.909
Did you hurt my dad?

1:11:07.877 --> 1:11:09.345
You're so pretty when you cry.

1:11:09.512 --> 1:11:11.947
You're such a good girl, Anna.

1:11:12.580 --> 1:11:14.316
So sweet and pure
in your nature.

1:11:14.517 --> 1:11:18.120
Stop it. Stop talking.

1:11:19.021 --> 1:11:20.356
I know
what you're going through.

1:11:20.923 --> 1:11:22.590
I've been there too.

1:11:24.126 --> 1:11:25.861
You deserve better
than your parents.

1:11:26.495 --> 1:11:27.662
You deserve love.

1:11:28.364 --> 1:11:29.865
My parents love me.

1:11:31.934 --> 1:11:33.302
Treat you like an afterbirth.

1:11:33.502 --> 1:11:35.337
That's not true.

1:11:36.072 --> 1:11:37.807
That's not true!

1:11:38.441 --> 1:11:39.842
You want to go
for a ride with me?

1:11:40.910 --> 1:11:41.910
No.

1:11:42.211 --> 1:11:43.879
But you don't even know
where I'm headed.

1:11:46.549 --> 1:11:48.683
I can show you things
you can't even dream of.

1:11:51.719 --> 1:11:53.355
Got a little boat
tied up out back.

1:11:53.688 --> 1:11:55.224
Grandpappy didn't even
know about it.

1:11:56.425 --> 1:11:59.895
We can disappear into the bayou.
No one will ever see us again.

1:12:01.430 --> 1:12:03.199
I don't make this
offer to many girls.

1:12:04.366 --> 1:12:06.035
It's a rare gem of an offer.

1:12:07.236 --> 1:12:08.236
Just like you.

1:12:10.005 --> 1:12:11.005
A rare gem.

1:12:14.510 --> 1:12:15.677
Anna!

1:12:29.125 --> 1:12:30.126
Mom!

1:12:31.227 --> 1:12:33.162
Let her go!

1:12:33.329 --> 1:12:36.298
Whoa, whoa. Whoa,
whoa. Can't do that, ma'am.

1:12:37.099 --> 1:12:39.568
See, I'm thinking about taking
your daughter here as my wife.

1:12:39.667 --> 1:12:40.936
Hardly seen a prettier girl.

1:12:41.070 --> 1:12:42.590
You'll go to hell
for what you've done.

1:12:42.637 --> 1:12:43.638
Been there already.

1:12:44.039 --> 1:12:45.808
Not much to see
compared to earth.

1:12:46.809 --> 1:12:49.245
Anna, stay strong.

1:12:50.712 --> 1:12:52.348
You know
why this happened, don't you?

1:12:53.015 --> 1:12:56.318
See, your husband hired me
and grandpappy to kill you.

1:13:00.089 --> 1:13:01.190
That's not true.

1:13:01.624 --> 1:13:02.657
Oh, sure it is.

1:13:03.125 --> 1:13:05.895
See, he thought
we were just country folk.

1:13:06.862 --> 1:13:08.864
Didn't understand
the nature of the beast.

1:13:10.665 --> 1:13:14.336
Truth is John's the one
who needed to be killed.

1:13:15.104 --> 1:13:16.104
Not you.

1:13:19.909 --> 1:13:21.310
Or your lovely, little Anna.

1:13:23.678 --> 1:13:24.847
Oh, fuck!

1:13:24.914 --> 1:13:26.248
Oh, fuck!

1:13:26.748 --> 1:13:28.284
No!

1:13:29.585 --> 1:13:30.786
Don't hurt my mom.

1:13:33.422 --> 1:13:34.657
Hey, hey.

1:13:34.722 --> 1:13:37.226
Hey.

1:13:39.795 --> 1:13:42.264
Hold on. Let's talk about this.

1:13:43.199 --> 1:13:46.602
If you're righteous,
you'll survive.

1:14:05.988 --> 1:14:09.925
I was just joshing
about marrying your daughter.

1:14:11.694 --> 1:14:13.761
From where I sit,

1:14:14.530 --> 1:14:16.232
marriage is just
a pit of spikes.

1:14:16.565 --> 1:14:18.100
Who the hell are you?

1:14:19.835 --> 1:14:22.705
I see myself as a moral compass.

1:14:23.138 --> 1:14:26.909
People spin
in the wrong direction,

1:14:27.343 --> 1:14:28.444
I set 'em straight.

1:14:33.215 --> 1:14:35.851
Me and the old man
built this house

1:14:36.452 --> 1:14:38.387
for people just like your husband.

1:14:39.754 --> 1:14:42.458
Murderers, liars, cheaters

1:14:43.359 --> 1:14:45.027
and sinners are all alike.

1:14:45.961 --> 1:14:47.762
They're drawn to it
like a magnet.

1:14:48.931 --> 1:14:50.332
It's my task to kill 'em.

1:14:50.866 --> 1:14:52.034
You're insane.

1:14:52.368 --> 1:14:55.070
I've been alive for centuries.

1:14:57.673 --> 1:14:58.974
Maybe I'm a demon.

1:15:00.042 --> 1:15:02.311
Or maybe I'm an angel.

1:15:03.579 --> 1:15:05.347
Or just a really confused kid.

1:15:22.564 --> 1:15:23.866
Here.

1:15:23.999 --> 1:15:26.068
Take 'em.

1:15:33.676 --> 1:15:35.878
Anna.

1:15:40.049 --> 1:15:41.250
Honey, Isaac's dying.

1:15:41.317 --> 1:15:43.118
- I'm fucking scared, mom.
- We have to go.

1:15:43.352 --> 1:15:44.920
Go. Go! We have to go.

1:15:44.987 --> 1:15:47.456
Everything's
gonna be okay. Run. Run! Run.

1:15:47.523 --> 1:15:49.992
Run. Run.

1:16:06.342 --> 1:16:09.378
Thank god.

1:16:20.656 --> 1:16:21.656
Check your phone.

1:16:21.924 --> 1:16:23.459
Check your phone
right now, please.

1:16:23.559 --> 1:16:26.195
Do you have a signal?

1:16:26.261 --> 1:16:28.664
I don't have any.
Why isn't it working, mom?

1:16:28.731 --> 1:16:30.232
It's not working.

1:16:30.466 --> 1:16:31.533
Did Isaac hurt you?

1:16:31.867 --> 1:16:33.435
Did he... did he touch you?

1:16:33.803 --> 1:16:35.738
- No.
- No?

1:16:36.071 --> 1:16:38.440
We left dad there, mom.

1:16:38.540 --> 1:16:41.377
We have to go back.
What about dad, mom?

1:16:41.477 --> 1:16:43.512
- What about... what about dad?
- What about dad?

1:16:43.612 --> 1:16:46.014
Listen to me. We're safe.

1:16:46.582 --> 1:16:49.786
That's what matters.
That we're safe right now.

1:16:49.853 --> 1:16:50.953
We're safe.

1:17:08.404 --> 1:17:10.706
And I keep telling you,
there are no houses out there.

1:17:11.006 --> 1:17:12.274
Not like the one you described.

1:17:12.541 --> 1:17:15.812
Yeah, something went wrong
with my phone and my computer

1:17:15.911 --> 1:17:18.213
and the pictures
aren't there anymore.

1:17:18.747 --> 1:17:20.115
It's not like
I don't believe you.

1:17:20.382 --> 1:17:23.485
We were inside that house.
I was the real estate agent.

1:17:23.585 --> 1:17:25.721
The house is real
and we need to find it

1:17:25.789 --> 1:17:26.789
and my husband.

1:17:27.055 --> 1:17:29.425
And we need to find Isaac
and... and the old man.

1:17:32.394 --> 1:17:36.165
- It's easy to get confused on the bayou.
- We're not confused.

1:17:36.698 --> 1:17:38.400
Isaac tried to kill us.

1:17:39.501 --> 1:17:41.370
And my dad is dead.

1:17:42.004 --> 1:17:44.173
Like I said,
deputies will be dispatched.

1:17:45.474 --> 1:17:46.985
Listen, I don't know
what really went on

1:17:47.009 --> 1:17:48.169
between you and your husband,

1:17:48.477 --> 1:17:50.145
but if he's out there, we'll find him.

1:17:50.345 --> 1:17:52.414
He's probably just disoriented.

1:17:52.981 --> 1:17:54.016
He may still be alive.

1:17:54.082 --> 1:17:56.786
You haven't heard a word I said.

1:17:56.920 --> 1:17:59.054
I heard you,
but you're not making any sense.

1:17:59.121 --> 1:18:00.456
Take me to this address.

1:18:01.023 --> 1:18:04.593
I wanna to see it myself.

1:18:05.060 --> 1:18:07.496
There are no homes around here.
It's just swamp.

1:18:08.564 --> 1:18:09.564
I'm ready when you are.

1:18:09.631 --> 1:18:11.767
And my daughter's
gonna stay here in the station.

1:18:12.000 --> 1:18:13.101
Mom...

1:18:13.837 --> 1:18:16.071
It's safer if I leave you here.

1:18:17.907 --> 1:18:19.041
Like you left dad?

1:18:19.909 --> 1:18:21.143
Is he safe?

1:18:26.950 --> 1:18:30.385
I promise, I will be back
in a couple hours.

1:19:38.821 --> 1:19:41.423
I swear, there was a house.

1:19:42.691 --> 1:19:46.194
It was... it was a big house.

1:19:50.098 --> 1:19:53.168
Uh. And there was a fire
in... in the driveway.

1:19:56.005 --> 1:19:57.139
Where?

1:19:57.472 --> 1:19:58.473
It was there.

1:20:00.043 --> 1:20:04.580
It was... it was...
It was right here.

1:20:05.280 --> 1:20:07.583
Like I said,
it's easy to get confused.

1:20:08.051 --> 1:20:10.053
I... I'm not confused. I'm not.

1:20:10.285 --> 1:20:12.922
Then you tell me,
are we at the wrong place?

1:20:13.221 --> 1:20:17.225
No. I don't know.

1:20:19.428 --> 1:20:22.364
Look, I'm happy to take you
somewhere else, within reason.

1:20:31.673 --> 1:20:33.375
It happened here.

1:21:27.797 --> 1:21:28.797
You're right.

1:21:35.872 --> 1:21:37.272
There's nothing here.

1:21:41.077 --> 1:21:42.344
There's no house.

1:21:46.983 --> 1:21:48.283
I'm sorry, ma'am.

1:21:52.989 --> 1:21:54.523
Take me back to the station.

1:22:09.204 --> 1:22:11.016
You know, to be honest,
you're not the first person

1:22:11.040 --> 1:22:12.307
to come to me with a crazy story

1:22:12.374 --> 1:22:13.608
about a house.

1:22:17.146 --> 1:22:18.647
Can you drive faster, please?

1:22:19.115 --> 1:22:20.549
First, I need you
to do me a favor.

1:22:20.749 --> 1:22:22.985
- What?
- Open the glove compartment.

1:22:31.094 --> 1:22:32.394
Oh, my god.

1:22:33.796 --> 1:22:35.965
But this was in the house.
How did you get it?

1:22:36.999 --> 1:22:38.901
That means
we have Isaac on tape.

1:22:39.468 --> 1:22:40.569
Turn it on.

1:22:43.873 --> 1:22:45.540
<i>We're right behind you, ma'am.</i>

1:22:50.278 --> 1:22:51.513
Oh, my god.

1:22:52.048 --> 1:22:54.483
Turn this off.

1:22:54.683 --> 1:22:56.518
It's on all the stations.

1:22:56.585 --> 1:22:58.921
That's not...
This can't be happening.

1:23:00.489 --> 1:23:05.393
<i>♪ Tell me the truth ♪</i>

1:23:06.528 --> 1:23:12.034
<i>♪ please stop me from guessing ♪</i>

1:23:14.636 --> 1:23:19.608
<i>♪ darling, it will be
a blessing ♪</i>

1:23:22.644 --> 1:23:26.082
<i>♪ if you will only
tell me the truth ♪</i>

1:23:29.051 --> 1:23:31.586
It was... them.

1:23:34.689 --> 1:23:35.689
Take a breath.

1:23:37.994 --> 1:23:38.994
It's not real.

1:23:40.362 --> 1:23:41.596
No, it can't be.

1:23:47.103 --> 1:23:49.504
Isaac and grandpappy
help us keep order.

1:23:51.207 --> 1:23:53.375
I don't know what they are.
They're not human.

1:23:54.376 --> 1:23:55.544
You're crazy.

1:23:57.013 --> 1:23:58.313
We protect Isaac,

1:23:58.680 --> 1:24:00.649
and he takes care
of the evildoers.

1:24:01.984 --> 1:24:04.020
Like a spider catching flies.

1:24:04.486 --> 1:24:06.022
He sends them straight to hell.

1:24:10.059 --> 1:24:11.093
It's an illusion.

1:24:11.260 --> 1:24:12.394
Tell yourself that.

1:24:12.761 --> 1:24:15.031
The bayou plays a lot of tricks.

1:24:18.366 --> 1:24:20.102
I'm gonna tell everyone
what happened.

1:24:20.735 --> 1:24:22.337
Who would believe you?

1:24:23.705 --> 1:24:26.575
Isaac doesn't hurt
the righteous, only the wicked.

1:24:29.444 --> 1:24:30.745
But I'm not wicked.

1:24:32.414 --> 1:24:33.850
It's a matter of degrees.

1:24:37.854 --> 1:24:39.688
Heaven and hell
are a choice away.

1:24:40.790 --> 1:24:43.993
Isaac gave you
a second chance. Embrace it.

1:24:45.127 --> 1:24:46.494
Be kind.

1:24:48.064 --> 1:24:50.765
And never come back
to the house on the bayou.

1:25:15.925 --> 1:25:17.093
- Anna?
- Mom.

1:25:17.260 --> 1:25:18.260
Anna.

1:25:19.128 --> 1:25:20.830
Oh, thank god.

1:25:21.330 --> 1:25:24.633
It's okay.

1:25:26.701 --> 1:25:28.403
I love you.

1:25:28.470 --> 1:25:29.638
Oh, honey.

1:25:30.639 --> 1:25:32.440
I'm never leaving you again.
